\title{Contextads for BCI control loops}
\taxon{definition}
\import{macros}

\p{Capucci-Myers' contextads ([[capucci-contextads-2024]]) give the
categorical structure underlying BCI control. A \strong{contextad} is
a dependent version of Para: morphisms carry context that varies with
the source.}

\p{In BCI, the context is the brain's current cognitive state. The decoder's
action depends on this context (dependent forward pass). The feedback
depends on both the action and the context (dependent backward pass).
This is a dependent optic ([[capucci-dependent-optics-2022]]) —
exactly the bidirectional structure needed for reafference (cf. [[bci-0003]]).}

\p{The wreath product decomposition #{Para \cong \int^{c : C} \mathrm{Hom}(c \otimes -, -)}
factors the control loop into:
\ul{
\li{\strong{Inner wreath}: the brain's autonomous dynamics (cofree comonad)}
\li{\strong{Outer wreath}: the decoder's control strategy (free monad)}
}
The wreath product is the composed system. Its fixed points are the
equilibria of the BCI game.}
